01:26:07.893 --> 01:26:09.724
We could go together, my dear,

01:26:09.828 --> 01:26:12.888
if you could bear to leave Alex
behind for a few weeks.

01:26:12.998 --> 01:26:15.899
I think I'd prefer Alex
to a case of seasickness.

01:26:18.670 --> 01:26:21.002
I always get seasick.

01:26:21.106 --> 01:26:25.236
Then you might like
the mountains, hmm?

01:26:25.343 --> 01:26:28.312
The air is fresh and pure and...

01:26:28.413 --> 01:26:30.313
I am going next week.

01:26:30.415 --> 01:26:33.942
Oh, you're leaving?
I'm sorry. I'll miss you.

01:26:34.052 --> 01:26:38.011
Yes. I'm delaying my work
too long.

01:26:38.123 --> 01:26:42.753
If you'll come with me,
the mountains won't make you seasick.

01:26:42.861 --> 01:26:47.025
And the Imorez Mountains are beautiful
covered with flowers and

01:26:47.132 --> 01:26:51.000
Oh, um, what Alicia needs
is rest, not mountain-climbing.

01:26:51.102 --> 01:26:53.696
I've heard about the Imorez.

01:26:53.805 --> 01:26:55.705
Did you? Really?

01:26:55.807 --> 01:26:58.776
Mmm, yes.

01:26:58.877 --> 01:27:01.505
About the beautiful
little native towns.

01:27:01.613 --> 01:27:03.911
Tell me,
are you going to Leopoldina?

01:27:04.015 --> 01:27:06.279
No, no, no.
I'm going to Santa Ma

01:27:06.384 --> 01:27:07.942
Care for some more brandy,
Otto?

01:27:08.053 --> 01:27:11.113
No, no, thank you.

01:27:11.222 --> 01:27:14.680
I, er, never drink more than one brandy,
and even this is sometimes too much.

01:27:14.793 --> 01:27:16.784
I'll just finish my coffee.

01:27:16.895 --> 01:27:19.159
No, that is not your cup!
But that's Ali

01:27:20.432 --> 01:27:22.525
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:27:22.634 --> 01:27:26.263
Yeah, perhaps, uh,
Alex is right, my dear child.

01:27:26.371 --> 01:27:28.737
When you're young,
rest's the best doctor.

01:27:30.575 --> 01:27:34.136
And if you...
lie still for a few days,

01:27:34.245 --> 01:27:37.476
reading, relaxing,
forgetting all your troubles,

01:27:37.582 --> 01:27:41.518
it might be as well as medicine
or sea air.

01:27:41.619 --> 01:27:43.985
When I come back,
you will be all well,

01:27:44.089 --> 01:27:45.989
making us all very happy once more.
Gasping

01:27:46.091 --> 01:27:47.991
Gasping Continues
Oh!

01:27:51.863 --> 01:27:54.855
Excuse me, II want to go to bed.
I feel

01:27:54.966 --> 01:27:58.925
Pain again, darling?
I'm sorry to complain again.

01:28:00.939 --> 01:28:03.737
Shall I take you
up to your room?

01:28:03.842 --> 01:28:05.742
May I help you, my dear?

01:28:05.844 --> 01:28:08.677
Some hot water, maybe?

01:28:10.515 --> 01:28:13.848
Gasps
No. No, please. Don't bother.

01:28:13.952 --> 01:28:16.250
I'll be all right.

01:28:16.354 --> 01:28:19.755
If she doesn't feel better in the
morning, I insist you call a doctor.

01:28:19.858 --> 01:28:22.383
I don't like
the way she looks, Alex.

01:28:22.494 --> 01:28:24.962
I'm worried about her.

01:28:25.063 --> 01:28:26.963
I'm afraid she's very ill.

01:28:27.065 --> 01:28:30.796
Chattering Continues, Indistinct

01:28:49.888 --> 01:28:51.788
Gasping

01:28:56.327 --> 01:28:58.591
Alicia! Alicia!
Joseph. Joseph.

01:28:58.696 --> 01:29:01.494
Help me take her up to her room.
You must take her up to bed.

01:29:01.599 --> 01:29:03.999
Come on, my dear.

01:29:10.442 --> 01:29:12.842
Okay. I told you she is sick.

01:29:12.944 --> 01:29:15.572
Come on.
Don't exert yourself. Come.

01:29:15.680 --> 01:29:18.171
Be quiet.

01:29:18.283 --> 01:29:22.515
No! Go! Go away!
No! No!

01:29:32.063 --> 01:29:34.531
Chattering, Indistinct
No, I don't want to go.

01:29:34.632 --> 01:29:37.692
It's some sort of spasm.
I'm sure it's not serious.

01:29:37.802 --> 01:29:39.827
We must get a doctor.

01:29:39.938 --> 01:29:42.930
Poor child is suffering too much.
I'll call the hospital.

01:29:43.041 --> 01:29:45.635
I'll get a doctor.
Don't worry, dear Otto.

01:29:45.743 --> 01:29:47.734
We'll get a doctor
a good one.

01:29:47.846 --> 01:29:50.246
We'll take
the best care of her.

01:29:50.348 --> 01:29:53.010
Sighing

01:29:53.118 --> 01:29:55.814
Sebastian
Joseph, disconnect the telephone.

01:29:55.920 --> 01:29:58.150
Madame must have absolute quiet.

01:29:58.256 --> 01:30:00.156
Take it out of the room, Joseph.

01:30:03.061 --> 01:30:04.961
Car Horns Honking

01:30:27.852 --> 01:30:29.683
Five days, eh?

01:30:29.787 --> 01:30:33.587
Say, that must be
quite a binge she's on.
I don't think so.

01:30:33.691 --> 01:30:36.751
Well, you said she was drinking
last week and drunk when you saw her.

01:30:36.861 --> 01:30:40.160
Yes, but I've had time
to think it over.
Think what over?

01:30:40.265 --> 01:30:42.825
That drinking of hers.
I don't believe it.

01:30:42.934 --> 01:30:45.767
Why should she lie to you
about that?

01:30:45.870 --> 01:30:47.770
I don't know.
She wasn't drunk.

01:30:47.872 --> 01:30:51.000
She was sick.
Maybe that's why she hasn't shown up.

01:30:51.109 --> 01:30:53.009
She looked like
the ragged end of nowhere.

01:30:53.111 --> 01:30:54.908
Well, it still sounds
like a hangover.

01:30:55.013 --> 01:30:57.447
Yes, but I'm gonna pay her a call.
Now, wait a minute.

01:30:57.549 --> 01:31:01.383
I don't want you to mess
things up. We hope to close
this case out in a few days.

01:31:01.486 --> 01:31:04.114
I won't mess anything up.
Just a social call.

01:31:04.222 --> 01:31:06.087
I, uh, I'm a friend
of the family.

01:31:06.191 --> 01:31:09.558
All right. Go ahead if you want to,
but don't take any chances.

01:31:09.661 --> 01:31:12.391
Oh, and, uh, call me up
when you get back.

01:31:12.497 --> 01:31:14.590
I'll do that.
'Kay.

01:31:40.158 --> 01:31:42.058
Good evening, sir.
Good evening.

01:31:42.160 --> 01:31:44.685
Family home tonight?
Yes, sir.

01:31:44.796 --> 01:31:48.061
Would you mind telling Mr. Sebastian
that Mr. Devlin is here?

01:31:49.500 --> 01:31:51.866
What is it, Joseph?
I'm very sorry, sir,

01:31:51.970 --> 01:31:56.100
but since Mr. Sebastian asked me
not to disturb him, I don't know.

01:31:56.207 --> 01:31:58.107
Asleep?
No, sir.

01:31:58.209 --> 01:32:00.609
He's in the study with
some business associates, sir.

01:32:00.712 --> 01:32:02.942
How long do you think
he'll be tied up?
I don't know, sir.

01:32:03.047 --> 01:32:05.982
Mrs. Sebastian home?
Uh, yes, sir.

01:32:06.084 --> 01:32:08.644
Would you mind telling her?
I'm afraid I can't, sir.

01:32:08.753 --> 01:32:12.553
Why not?
Mrs. Sebastian is very ill
and confined to her bed.

01:32:14.259 --> 01:32:16.750
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.
How long has she been ill?

01:32:16.861 --> 01:32:19.056
A week.
Has she had a doctor?

01:32:19.163 --> 01:32:22.997
I think so, sir.
We're all very concerned about her.

01:32:23.101 --> 01:32:26.730
If you will wait here, Mr. Devlin,
I'll tell Mr. Sebastian.

01:32:26.838 --> 01:32:28.738
Right.

01:32:35.647 --> 01:32:37.877
Excuse me, sir.
What is it, Joseph?

01:32:37.982 --> 01:32:40.314
Mr. Devlin to see you, sir.

01:32:40.418 --> 01:32:43.979
Oh. Tell him I'll be with him
in a minute, will you?

01:32:44.088 --> 01:32:45.988
Yes, sir.

01:32:47.592 --> 01:32:50.493
Go on, Professor.
This sounds serious to me.

01:32:50.595 --> 01:32:53.428
To me also.
What happened Monday?

01:32:53.531 --> 01:32:55.431
Same thing.

01:32:55.533 --> 01:32:58.229
When I left the bank,
a man was following me.

01:32:58.336 --> 01:33:01.533
But this morning, when I went
to the ticket office,

01:33:01.639 --> 01:33:04.870
the same man came inside
and stood beside me.

01:33:54.826 --> 01:33:56.726
Door Closes

01:34:11.509 --> 01:34:13.875
Alicia. Alicia.

01:34:18.449 --> 01:34:20.417
Weakly
Dev.

01:34:21.686 --> 01:34:23.586
Alicia,
what's wrong with you?

01:34:23.688 --> 01:34:25.849
I'm so glad you came.

01:34:27.992 --> 01:34:31.621
I had to.
I couldn't stand any more...

01:34:31.729 --> 01:34:33.720
waiting and worrying about you.

01:34:34.899 --> 01:34:37.424
That wasn't a hangover
you had that day.

01:34:37.535 --> 01:34:40.527
You were sick then.
What is it?

01:34:40.638 --> 01:34:42.697
Yes, I was sick.

01:34:44.242 --> 01:34:46.676
What's wrong with you, Alicia?

01:34:46.778 --> 01:34:50.214
Oh, Dev.
What is it, dear?
What's wrong with you?

01:34:52.383 --> 01:34:54.510
They're poisoning me.

01:34:54.619 --> 01:34:57.213
I couldn't get away from them.

01:34:57.321 --> 01:34:59.414
I tried, but I was too weak.

01:34:59.524 --> 01:35:01.424
How long?

01:35:02.727 --> 01:35:05.195
Since the party.

01:35:05.296 --> 01:35:07.628
Alex and his mother found out.

01:35:12.103 --> 01:35:14.230
Come on. Try and sit up.

01:35:14.338 --> 01:35:17.501
Sit up. I'm going
to get you out of here.

01:35:17.608 --> 01:35:20.202
I thought you had gone.

01:35:20.311 --> 01:35:23.769
No. I had to see you once,
speak my piece.

01:35:23.881 --> 01:35:26.372
I was getting out
because I love you.

01:35:26.484 --> 01:35:28.884
I couldn't bear
seeing you and him together.

01:35:35.993 --> 01:35:38.154
Oh, you love me.

01:35:38.262 --> 01:35:41.163
Why didn't you tell me before?

01:35:41.265 --> 01:35:43.165
I know.

01:35:43.267 --> 01:35:45.735
But I couldn't see straight
or think straight.

01:35:46.871 --> 01:35:50.671
I was a fatheaded guy,
full of pain.

01:35:50.775 --> 01:35:52.675
It tore me up not having you.

01:35:55.680 --> 01:35:57.580
Oh, you love me.

01:35:58.816 --> 01:36:00.716
Oh, you love me.

01:36:00.818 --> 01:36:03.150
Long ago. All the time,
since the beginning.

01:36:07.592 --> 01:36:09.492
Here, put on your robe.

01:36:11.295 --> 01:36:13.786
Come on.
Yes.

01:36:13.898 --> 01:36:16.128
Try to sit up.
Yes.

01:36:17.969 --> 01:36:20.301
Oh, Dev. I'm afraid...

01:36:20.404 --> 01:36:25.000
I can't make it because
they gave me pills to sleep.

01:36:25.109 --> 01:36:27.669
Keep awake. Keep talking.

01:36:27.778 --> 01:36:30.338
Yes.
Have you got a coat?

01:36:30.448 --> 01:36:32.746
In the closet.

01:36:32.850 --> 01:36:35.512
They didn't want
the others to know about me.

01:36:42.426 --> 01:36:44.326
Keep talking.

01:36:48.533 --> 01:36:51.024
Go on. What happened?

01:36:51.135 --> 01:36:54.161
What happened?
Alex found out.

01:36:54.272 --> 01:36:58.936
And the others haven't?
They'd kill him if they knew.

01:36:59.043 --> 01:37:01.511
They killed Emil.

01:37:01.612 --> 01:37:05.571
Are you in pain?
I don't know. The pills.

01:37:05.683 --> 01:37:07.708
Give me your feet.
Yes.

01:37:09.487 --> 01:37:12.354
Say it again.
It keeps me awake.

01:37:12.456 --> 01:37:15.050
I love you.

01:37:15.159 --> 01:37:17.252
Stand up. Stand up.

01:37:17.361 --> 01:37:20.853
Oh.
Come on. Wake up. Talk.

01:37:20.965 --> 01:37:24.230
Dr. Anderson

01:37:24.335 --> 01:37:26.269
Go on, go on. Walk, talk.

01:37:26.370 --> 01:37:31.034
The sand comes
from the Imorez Mountains.

01:37:31.142 --> 01:37:33.042
We'll find it.

01:37:33.144 --> 01:37:35.942
From a town
Santa Ma-something.

01:37:36.047 --> 01:37:38.174
Good girl.
We'll take care of it later.

01:37:38.282 --> 01:37:40.546
Come on. Keep awake. Keep walking.
Oh, I'm afraid!

01:37:40.651 --> 01:37:43.552
Dev, I'm afraid. They're all
in the house. We can't make it.

01:37:51.128 --> 01:37:53.460
Oh, don't ever leave me.

01:37:53.564 --> 01:37:55.964
You'll never
get rid of me again.

01:37:57.234 --> 01:37:59.600
Never tried to.

01:37:59.704 --> 01:38:01.501
Brace up. Here he comes.

01:38:06.744 --> 01:38:09.975
What are you doing, Alicia?
What is this, Mr. Devlin?

01:38:10.081 --> 01:38:12.811
I'm taking her to the hospital
to get the poison out of her.

01:38:12.917 --> 01:38:16.353
Poison?
How'd you like your friends
downstairs to know?

01:38:16.454 --> 01:38:18.888
They've yet to be told.
I'm taking her back to her room.

01:38:18.990 --> 01:38:21.652
No, Dev. I'll raise
quite a rumpus, if you try.

01:38:21.759 --> 01:38:25.024
Alex. He knows?

01:38:25.129 --> 01:38:27.063
Yes.
Dr. Anderson
What is happening, Alex?

01:38:29.100 --> 01:38:31.796
Alicia!
She is worse?

01:38:31.902 --> 01:38:33.961
Mrs. Sebastian Yes.
Go.

01:38:34.071 --> 01:38:36.301
All right, dear.
We're going. We're going.

01:38:36.407 --> 01:38:39.865
You haven't forgotten what they did
to Emil, have you, Sebastian?

01:38:42.847 --> 01:38:45.645
Whispering
Help him, Alex.

01:38:45.750 --> 01:38:48.548
I'm glad you
have a head on you, madame.

01:38:48.653 --> 01:38:51.315
I'm not afraid to die.

01:38:51.422 --> 01:38:54.482
You've got your chance here and now.
Tell them who she is.

01:38:55.926 --> 01:38:58.520
Need any help, Alex?

01:38:58.629 --> 01:39:00.927
No, we can handle her.
Where are you taking her?

01:39:03.601 --> 01:39:07.059
You answer that one, Sebastian.
To the hospital.

01:39:07.171 --> 01:39:09.571
Whispering
Alex, talk to them, quick!

01:39:14.679 --> 01:39:16.613
Glad she's going.

01:39:16.714 --> 01:39:18.614
You should not have waited
so long, Alex.

01:39:21.318 --> 01:39:23.684
Well, what am I going to do,
start shooting?

01:39:26.057 --> 01:39:28.184
Hold on. You've only got
about 20 yards to go.

01:39:28.292 --> 01:39:31.056
What happened, Alex?
Hmm?

01:39:32.663 --> 01:39:37.259
Oh, um... she collapsed.

01:39:37.368 --> 01:39:41.634
Mr. Devlin heard her scream when he
was waiting for me. Come on, Alicia.

01:39:41.739 --> 01:39:45.573
Yes, I telephoned the hospital
as soon as I saw how she was.

01:39:45.676 --> 01:39:47.644
You have a car? You heard, Alex.
Out in front.

01:39:47.745 --> 01:39:49.736
You're going with them, madame?

01:39:49.847 --> 01:39:53.783
No. Alex will call me up.
I'll wait here.

01:39:53.884 --> 01:39:56.318
Chatters, Indistinct

01:39:56.420 --> 01:39:58.320
Poor child.

01:40:00.758 --> 01:40:03.556
How do you feel?
A bit dizzy.

01:40:03.661 --> 01:40:06.152
Take some deep breaths.
Just hurry, hurry.

01:40:17.374 --> 01:40:20.571
Now just a minute.
I must sit with her!
No room, Sebastian.

01:40:20.678 --> 01:40:23.112
But you must take me.
They're watching me.
That's your headache.

01:40:23.214 --> 01:40:24.613
Engine Starts
Please take me! Please!

01:40:24.715 --> 01:40:27.775
Please! Please!

01:40:27.885 --> 01:40:31.685
There is no telephone
in her room to call the hospital.

01:40:31.789 --> 01:40:35.190
Eric
Alex, will you come in, please?

01:40:35.292 --> 01:40:37.192
I wish to talk to you.

